      "side": 1,
      "message": "RDE device can have many Redfish Resource PDR that report `ContainingResourceID\u003d0`  (0 in this case means \"EXTERNAL: This value is used to identify the logical root of a device component’s management topology\"). For example SmartNIC device can simultaniously report Redfish Resources that should be added to the different \"root\" collections on the server side:\n- `NetworkAdapterCollecion`\n- `NetworkIntefaceCollection`\n- `PCIeDeviceCollection`\n- `EthernetInterfaceCollecion`\n\nSo in other words just `TargetURI` is not enough, since all these resources will have \"/\" URI in this case.",
      "revId": "9f6802c2a6ccebc9ed80348436a0e52ab5c15a06",
